.TH CR-BASH 1 "March 2026" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
cr-bash \- create a new Bash script with shebang and open it in editor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cr-bash
[options] filepath/filename
.SH DESCRIPTION
Creates a new Bash script at the specified path.

If parent directories do not exist, they are created automatically.

The file is initialized with:
  - A shebang line: #!/usr/bin/env bash
  - Two empty lines

The file is made executable.

If the file already exists, the command aborts.

The file is opened in your default editor (\$EDITOR or vim).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
-h, --help
Show usage information
.TP
-v, --version
Show version information
.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns 1 if:
  - No argument is provided
  - The file already exists
  - Directory creation fails
